s in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Hugh De Essex I married Hugh De Essex I before 1148, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1117–Male":"1117–Surnud","1148–1194":"1148–1194","–Female":"Surnud","1117":"1117","before 1148":"enne 1148","1148":"1148","1194":"1194","um 1148":"umbes 1148","England":"England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1117–Male":"1117–Kuollut","1148–1194":"1148–1194","–Female":"Kuollut","1117":"1117","before 1148":"ennen vuotta 1148","1148":"1148","1194":"1194","um 1148":"noin 1148","England":"England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1117–Male":"1117–Décédé","1148–1194":"1148–1194","–Female":"Décédée","1117":"1117","before 1148":"avant 1148","1148":"1148","1194":"1194","um 1148":"environ 1148","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs Hugh De Essex I a épousé Hugh De Essex I avant 1148, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1117–Male":"1117–Verstorben","1148–1194":"1148–1194","–Female":"Verstorben","1117":"1117","before 1148":"vor 1148","1148":"1148","1194":"1194","um 1148":"um 1148","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Mrs Hugh De Essex I hat vor 1148 in England Hugh De Essex I geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1117–Male":"1117–Desede","1148–1194":"1148–1194","–Female":"Desede","1117":"1117","before 1148":"before 1148","1148":"1148","1194":"1194","um 1148":"about 1148","England":"England"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","1117–Male":"1117–elhunyt","1148–1194":"1148–1194","–Female":"elhunyt","1117":"1117","before 1148":"1